sentences: William S. Schnee (born July 4, 1947) is an American musician, music producer, and audio engineer.
In 1964, his senior year at Glendora High School, Schnee started a band, The LA Teens, writing songs and playing organ.

Schnee was instrumental in launching Sheffield Lab Records and the modern era direct to disc audiophile recordings, when in 1975 he produced the Thelma Houston and Pressure Cooker album, I've Got the Music in Me.
In 1981, Schnee opened Schnee Studio in North Hollywood.
In 2015, Schnee Studio was sold and merged to become Studio 6 of the adjacent Larrabee Sound Studios.
1992 Outstanding Achievement in Sound Mixing For a Variety, Music series, or Special for "Unforgettable, With Love" by Natalie Cole.
1995 Praise and Worship Album of the Year for Promise Keepers, Raise the Standard.
In a 45+ year career of very diverse artists, Schnee has received over 135 gold and platinum records and has recorded/mixed over 50 top twenty singles.

Three years after being produced by Podolor, Schnee's big break came when he was hired to engineer in Podolor's studio.
On Schnee's third day, Podolor put him in to record two tracks and some overdubs for Three Dog Night.
